_Save

protected void _Save(DtoType p_entity)
Make persistent a single entity. If the entity has id, update its values. Otherwise create it and set the created id. A quick example: Book book = new Book("title", 19.99); _Save(book); System.out.println(book.GetId()); // this will print the created id

Parameters:
p_entity -

_DeleteByLongIds

protected void _DeleteByLongIds(Iterable<Long> p_ids)
Deletes the specified entities in a parallel batch operation. This is faster and more efficient than deleting them one by one. A quick example: List<Long> ids = new ArrayList<Long>(); ids.add(14545); ids.add(14546); _DeleteByLongIds(ids);

Parameters:
p_ids - contain Long identifiers.
